<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3689] RegionServers should not check-in to Master until they are fully available</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3689</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Over in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3687&quot; title=&quot;Bulk assign on startup should handle a ServerNotRunningException&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3687&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3687&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, a Master tripped over a RegionServer that had checked in but had not yet finished initializing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since a master only learns of an RS after it sends an RPC, we should have the RS only send the RPC once it is done initializing / ready to take on regions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
